<paragraph id="8C3043EE974BA90856D3A8A0647AC128" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="E3D5EFAADDEDE0C31F0EFA9C8E53D885" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Carapace</emphasis>
: slightly longer than broad (1.00-1.01 
<normalizedToken id="857EA517090FC25A6EEAB5F355DD2651" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
), anterior margin with 4 setae, posterior margin with 12-13 setae. Well-developed paramedian impressions behind eyes like in male. 
<emphasis id="9E562C6C3F22E4A53FDAFEC69D9AAB92" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Coxae</emphasis>
: pedipalpal coxa with 9 (non-denticulate) + 4-6 (denticulate) setae, coxa I 20-21, II 18, III 17-19, IV 52-55. 
<emphasis id="652C1E74A3CD3B86DFF2E63030D46239" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Chelicera</emphasis>
: 1.94-1.97 
<normalizedToken id="59AA3F6420E01A6BCD54362BE4F6156E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, movable finger with 2-3 teeth. 
<emphasis id="F5D86EF3B2460DAF2E3BDD3E99E09F46" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Pedipalp</emphasis>
: trochanter 2.03-2.05 
<normalizedToken id="B2C0F3531185E71FA44C342C8A7DAE20" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, femur 6.18-6.21 
<normalizedToken id="624182BDFF9A7E4AACC86BDE11182F56" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, patella 4.81-4.86 
<normalizedToken id="1DB21F1BA8BE39BEACB66D79728F1187" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, femur 1.16-1.17 
<normalizedToken id="B60C3349FFBAAA3B1E732EEF13F5773F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than patella. Chela with pedicel 5.10-5.11 
<normalizedToken id="5677FF0098776DC4E9D5658B135A0C7B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, hand with pedicel 2.51-2.53 
<normalizedToken id="2D072917A605DED5C2FAAE2903E62088" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad; movable finger 1.01-1.02 
<normalizedToken id="BD7222288C3B403D349642806897D839" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than hand with pedicel length. 
<emphasis id="59DF2C8E66E1347335176AAF846A7B69" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Opisthosoma</emphasis>
: tergal chaetotaxy (I-XI): 15: 18: 20: 24: 23: 25: 25: 26: 23: 16: 15; sternal chaetotaxy (IV-XI): 2 
<normalizedToken id="63012D23EDC6FF9CB4857A6958FB70A4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1 + 11: 15: 15: 15: 13: 14: 13: 10; anal cone with 2 dorsal and 2 ventral setae. Anterior genital operculum with 28 setae (without tubular setae) and 2 lyrifissures; posterior operculum with 13 setae, 8 lyrifissures (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F2967ADFF57945F3C340EB9D03D3CF2F" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Metachelifer mahnerti sp. nov., holotype male (A-I) and paratype female (J) A carapace B left chelicera C rallum of left chelicera D detail on tarsus I, lateral view E coxa IV, ventral view F palp (minus chela) G chela, retrolateral view H chela, dorsal view I male genital area J female genital area. Scale bars: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.78808.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691635" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">2J</figureCitation>
). Sternites with 2 lateral cribriform plates.
</paragraph>
